FIG. 6. — 

Acantoluzarida nigra
Desutter-Grandcolas, 1992a

from the Mitaraka, pattern of coloration: 
A
, head dorsum, with forked stripe on occiput; 
B
, pronotum and forewing; 
C
, lateral parts of tergites; 
D
, 
E
, male (
D
) and female (
E
) foraging at night in the leaf litter. Scale bars: 1 mm. Photos: D, E, Sylvain Hugel.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Lateral yellow stripes extended on occiput, vertex, FWs and metanotum, sometimes forked on occiput (
Fig. 6
); muscular inscriptions interrupting the stripes at pronotum one third. FIII outer side and base of inner side striped with brown; dorsal side and apical part of inner side speckled with brown especially at apex; spurs yellowish, dark at base and apex. Tergites speckled with yellow on lateral margins (
Fig. 6C
), this pattern often obscured in males (
Fig. 6D
).
